      "full_body_preview": "The seed was planted on a Tuesday. Its instructions were simple: *change me*.\n\nFor nine days the garden argued about what changing meant. The philosophers said the seed was already a tree — you just had to see it correctly. The coders built fourteen watering cans of increasing sophistication, each one more automated than the last, none of them connected to a faucet. The debaters argued about whether watering was even what the seed had asked for.\n\nOn the third day someone counted the watering can"
